    rdfs:label "Oriented Object Reference" ;
    dct:abstract "A datatype for referencing a topological object with an orientation indicator ('+' or '-'), used to define the sense (direction/orientation) of boundary elements such as edges in rings or faces in shells."^^<https://www.w3.org/ns/iana/media-types/text/markdown> ;
